Package extended_mitre.capec

Class CAPECobject

  • java.lang.Object
    • extended_mitre.capec.CAPECobject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    @Entity(name="capec")
public class CAPECobject
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class represents a CAPEC attack pattern object (CAPEC ID, name, abstraction attribute, status, ...)

    It can parse CAPEC attack pattern objects from given XML file It uses DOM XML parser

    Objects can be put into database

    It can also create a CAPEC attack pattern object from given parameters and return it

    Author:
    Tomas Bozek (XarfNao)
    See Also:

        capec_id - ID of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        capec_name - name of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        capec_abstraction - abstraction attribute of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        capec_status - status of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        description - description of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        attack_likelihood - likelihood of attack attribute of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        typical_severity - typical severity attribute of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        cwe - relating CWE weaknesses for a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        mitigations - mitigation attributes of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        prerequisites - prerequisite attributes of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        examples - example attributes of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        resources - resources required for a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        indicators - indicators of a specific attack pattern (CAPEC)
        notes - note objects of a specific CAPEC object
        tax_maps - taxonomy mapping objects of a specific CAPEC object
        alter_terms - alternate term objects of a specific CAPEC object
        ext_ref_refs - external reference reference objects of a specific CAPEC object
        consequences - consequence objects of a specific CAPEC object
        related_patterns - related CAPEC attack patterns - relation objects
        attack_steps - attack step objects (execution flow) of a specific CAPEC object
        skills_required - skills required attribute of a specific CAPEC object - skill objects

      • CAPECfileToArrayList

        public static java.util.List<CAPECobject> CAPECfileToArrayList​(java.lang.String capec_file,
                                                               java.util.List<CWEextRefObj> ext_refs)
        This method's purpose is to parse and create a List of CAPEC attack pattern objects from given XML file which contains them

        It uses DOM XML parser

        It goes through file that contains latest list of CAPEC attack patterns, parses them and returns them in a List

        Parameters:
        capec_file - path to .xml file with CAPEC data
        ext_refs - existing External Reference objects for search of the relating ones
        Returns:
        List of CAPEC attack pattern objects from given XML file
